reviews.text: Ridiculous location (more than half mile from the airport) with even more ridiculous service to match (only one train in each direction per WEEK actually stops here). Not surprisingly, the station is one of the least used in the country and looks as if it's falling apart at the seams. Unless the sole reason for visiting is to say you've been here, as suggested by a previous reviewer, then really it's not worth the effort.
One of the least used railway stations in the country. Worth a visit just to say you've been.
I’m only giving it five stars because you could just come here for some peace
It is a very nice and senic station and is very quaint
For a station located near en "International" airport. It isn't very busy most of the times. You're going to be suprised if you see some one else in this station.
